description:
## Issue

Magic numbers are defined locally in multiple files, reducing code readability and maintainability.

## Locations

- src/server/integrations/igdb/IGDBClient.ts:176-177 - batchSize=10, parallelLimit=4
- src/server/services/DownloadService.ts:31,316-317 - delays array values

## Fix

Extract to named constants at module level:

```typescript
// IGDBClient.ts
const IGDB_BATCH_SIZE = 10;
const IGDB_PARALLEL_LIMIT = 4;

// DownloadService.ts
const RETRY_DELAYS_MS = [1000, 2000, 4000] as const;
// or
const INITIAL_RETRY_DELAY_MS = 1000;
const RETRY_DELAY_MULTIPLIER = 2;
```

This makes the purpose of these numbers clear and allows easy adjustment.

DownloadService.syncDownloadStatus() (lines 229-232) uses naive substring match (first 20 chars) to correlate torrents with releases:

const torrent = torrents.find((t) =>
  t.name.toLowerCase().includes(release.title.toLowerCase().substring(0, 20))
);

This causes sync failures for similar names or multi-game downloads.

Fix: Store torrent hash when adding to qBittorrent and use hash-based matching.

Every route has identical try-catch blocks with the same error formatting (70+ occurrences):

try { ... } catch (error) {
  logger.error('Operation failed:', error);
  return c.json({ success: false, error: error instanceof Error ? error.message : 'Unknown error' }, 500);
}

Fix: Create error handling middleware or utility function.

Some routes validate parseInt() for NaN but others don't, creating inconsistency:

Good (search.ts lines 33-36):
const id = parseInt(c.req.param('id'));
if (isNaN(id)) return c.json({ success: false, error: 'Invalid ID' }, 400);

Missing: indexers.ts, parts of updates.ts

Fix: Add consistent NaN validation after all parseInt() calls for route parameters.

## Issue

Database files use console.log directly instead of the centralized logger utility, resulting in inconsistent logging format and behavior.

## Locations

- src/server/db/index.ts:30,166
- src/server/db/migrate.ts:8,12

## Fix

Replace console.log calls with the centralized logger:

```typescript
import { logger } from '../utils/logger';

// Instead of:
console.log('Database initialized');

// Use:
logger.info('Database initialized', { component: 'database' });
```

This ensures consistent log formatting, levels, and potential future enhancements like log aggregation.

steam.ts uses 'any' for SSE send function (line 320):

const send = (data: any) => { ... }

Fix: Define proper SSEProgressEvent, SSECompleteEvent, SSEErrorEvent types.
